Pascale Ogier https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pascale_Ogier 0 Pascale Marguerite Cécile Claude Colette Nicolas (26 October 1958 – 25 October 1984), better known as Pascale Ogier, was a French actress. She won the Volpi Cup and posthumously received a César Award nomination for her role in the 1984 film Full Moon in Paris.
